<title>SPAIN: Peseta debt/interbank closing report.</title>
<headline>Peseta debt/interbank closing report.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-07-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spanish government bonds shifted sharply lower late on Thursday, tracking losses on sister markets after the July Chicago purchasing managers' index outstripped expectations, dealers said.</p>
<p>The prices paid index came in at 61.6, its highest level for two years, causing knee-jerk selling on inflation fears. But analysts said the data was an excuse to sell in a thin and edgy market in which fresh factors have been lacking recently.</p>
<p>&quot;The (Chicago PMI) is really the only price indicator which has been bad in the past few months,&quot; said Juan Antonio Mielgo, economist at Bank of America in Madrid.</p>
